# VehicleOS Git & PR Workflow

Repository: `karantyagi/VehicleOS` (local path may be `github repo/VehicleOS`).

## Default branch

**`master`** — never target `main` unless the user explicitly says the default changed.

## Before every new feature branch

Run in order:

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout master
git pull origin master
git checkout -b <type>/<area>-<short-name>
```

Do not create feature branches from other feature branches unless the user explicitly requests a stacked PR.

## Branch naming

`<type>/<area>-<short-name>`

- `feature/` — product or user-facing work
- `chore/` — CI, tooling, repo standards
- `docs/` — documentation only
- `fix/` — bug fixes

Examples: `feature/apps-marketing-landing`, `chore/dev-workflow-repo-standards`

## Scope and commits

- One feature per PR; do not mix unrelated areas
- Never commit: `.env`, secrets, `node_modules/`, `.next/`, build artifacts
- Commit only when the user asks (unless their instructions say to ship a PR)
- Subject: imperative, concise. Body: why, not a file inventory

## Pre-PR verification

Build apps affected by the change:

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm --filter @vehicleos/marketing build   # if marketing changed
pnpm --filter @vehicleos/web build           # if web changed
```

## Pull requests

- Use **`gh`** for all GitHub operations (PR create, comments, checks)
- Base branch: **`master`**
- Title: clear outcome (e.g. `Add Phase A marketing site (recruiter landing)`)
- Body: follow `.github/pull_request_template.md` (Summary, Type, Apps affected, Test plan)
- Push: `git push -u origin HEAD`
- Create: `gh pr create --base master --title "..." --body "..."`
- Do not merge unless the user explicitly asks

## Parallel work

- Independent apps: branch from `master` in parallel
- Overlapping files (`README.md`, `package.json`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`): merge or rebase first
- If `master` advanced: `git fetch origin && git rebase origin/master` on the feature branch

